msgid "include::ROOT::partial$under-construction.adoc[]"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-publishing/modules/ROOT/pages/LSDI-lookup.adoc:15
msgid "GBIF processes taxonomic identifiers that are provided on the DwC elements _scientificNameID_, _taxonID_ and _taxonConceptID_, when these identifiers belong to any of the identifier schemes available. The identifiers are retrieved from ChecklistBank and linked to taxa in the checklist, currently the schemes available are:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-publishing/modules/ROOT/pages/LSDI-lookup.adoc:17
msgid "https://artfakta.se/metadata/dyntaxa[Dyntaxa]: A taxonomic database of the names of Swedish organisms, contains information on current classification, recommended names and commonly used synonyms and misused names. It should follow the format: `+^(?:dyntaxa|artfakta|urn:lsid:dyntaxa.se:Taxon):(\\\\d+)`+"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-publishing/modules/ROOT/pages/LSDI-lookup.adoc:18
msgid "https://www.ipni.org/[IPNI]: The International Plant Names Index (IPNI) is a nomenclatural index of names of vascular plants published under the Code of Nomenclature for algae, fungi and plants (ICN).  It should follow the format: `+^(?:ipni|urn:lsid:ipni.org:names):(\\\\d+-[1-3])`+"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-publishing/modules/ROOT/pages/LSDI-lookup.adoc:19
msgid "https://www.itis.gov/p[ITIS]: The Integrated Taxonomic Information System, an authoritative taxonomic information on plants, animals, fungi, and microbes of North America and the world. It should follow the format: `+^(?:itis|tsn:)(\\\\d+)`+"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-publishing/modules/ROOT/pages/LSDI-lookup.adoc:20
msgid "https://www.nhm.ac.uk/our-science/data/uk-species/index[UK Species Inventory]: A database of all UK wildlife, it provides the taxonomic foundation for most biological recording and analysis systems for the UK. It should follow the format: `+^(?:uksi|nhm):((?:NHMSYS|NBNSYS)\\\\d{10})`+"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-publishing/modules/ROOT/pages/LSDI-lookup.adoc:21
msgid "https://www.marinespecies.org/index.php[WoRMs]: The World Register of Marine Species (WoRMS) aim to provide an authoritative and comprehensive list of names of marine organisms, including information on synonymy. It should follow the format: `+^(?:marinespecies|worms|aphia|urn:lsid:marinespecies.org:taxname):(\\\\d+)`+"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-publishing/modules/ROOT/pages/LSDI-lookup.adoc:23
msgid "When both an identifier field and a _scientificName_ are provided, the identifier field will be used first for matching. A match will also be made using the scientificName and a comparison will be made between the two matches. When there are identifiers present, the following issues could be arise:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-publishing/modules/ROOT/pages/LSDI-lookup.adoc:25
msgid "‘Scientific name and ID inconsistent’: When the information in _scientificName_ and any of the identifiers do not agree."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-publishing/modules/ROOT/pages/LSDI-lookup.adoc:26
msgid "‘Scientific name ID not found’, ‘Taxon concept ID not found’ or ‘Taxon ID not found’: An identifier is provided and match the known pattern of the schemes available, but it is not found in the associated checklist."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-publishing/modules/ROOT/pages/LSDI-lookup.adoc:27
msgid "‘Taxon match scientific name ID ignored’, ‘Taxon match taxon concept ID ignored’ or ‘Taxon match taxon ID ignored’: An identifier is provided but does not match the known pattern of the schemes available."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-publishing/modules/ROOT/pages/LSDI-lookup.adoc:28
msgid "‘Taxon match name and ID ambiguous‘: When the concept was found using any of the identifiers, but it differs from what would have been found if the classification names on the record were used."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-publishing/modules/ROOT/pages/LSDI-lookup.adoc:29
msgid "You can read the full description of the issues here: https://techdocs.gbif.org/en/data-use/occurrence-issues-and-flags#taxonomic-issues[Taxonomic issues] and the detailed technical information about Taxonomic indexes is available on: https://techdocs.gbif.org/en/data-processing/taxonomy-interpretation#taxonomic-indexes[Taxonomy interpretation - Taxonomic indexes]."
msgstr ""

